This project uses MySQL as the database engine. Follow the steps below to set up your environment and connect the application to the database.

ğŸ”§ Prerequisites
- Install XAMPP (includes MySQL & phpMyAdmin).
- Install MySQL Connector for your programming language (e.g., mysql-connector-python for Python).
pip install mysql-connector-python



ğŸ—„ï¸ Database Setup in XAMPP
- Start Apache and MySQL from the XAMPP Control Panel.
- Open phpMyAdmin in your browser:
http://localhost/phpmyadmin
- Create a new database (e.g., my_project_db).

ğŸ“‘ Create Tables
Users Table
CREATE TABLE users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE,
    password VARCHAR(255),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    created_at DATETIME,
    last_login DATETIME
);


Predictions Table
CREATE TABLE predictions (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50),
    prediction VARCHAR(50),
    confidence FLOAT,
    timestamp DATETIME
);



